## **The One Critical Addition: Voice Mode Should Be Persona-Dependent**\
\
Here's what the advisor's framework is missing:\
\
**Not all personas need relatable first-person.**\
\
### **Persona Risk Matrix**\
\
| Persona | Primary Concern | Voice Mode Recommendation |\
|---------|----------------|---------------------------|\
| Gen Z Professionals | Burnout, anxiety | Relatable FP (high value) |\
| Gen Z Students | Academic stress | Relatable FP (high value) |\
| Healthcare Workers | Compassion fatigue | Wisdom Voice (safety first) |\
| Parents | Overwhelm | Wisdom Voice (authority needed) |\
| Executives | Leadership stress | Wisdom Voice (credibility matters) |\
| Chronic Pain | Body awareness | Wisdom Voice (clinical trust) |\
\
**Why this matters:**\
\
Gen Z research shows they want **peer voice** because they distrust hierarchy and want relatable lived experience.\
\
But:\
- **Healthcare workers** need clinical authority (not peer voice)\
- **Parents** need confident guidance (not "I'm figuring this out too")\
- **Executives** need credibility (peer voice feels unprofessional)\
\
