## Executive Summary\
\
### What We're Building\
\
A structured content template system that makes chapter points land harder through strategic positioning and punctuation-based emphasis.\
\
**Three-Beat Structure:**\
1. **Seed** (early chapter) - Implicit recognition that plants emotional soil\
2. **Experience** (at exercise) - Somatic learning through body practice\
3. **Name** (post-exercise) - Explicit statement of chapter point when listener is receptive\
\
### Why We're Building It\
\
Current chapter points are clear but feel "too quickly stated" because:\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u10060 
\f0  Appear as single-line statements buried in paragraph flow\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u10060 
\f0  No emotional weight or strategic positioning\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u10060 
\f0  Stated once then moved on from\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u10060 
\f0  Don't leverage the receptive state post-exercise\
\
Research shows therapeutic content lands better when:\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Implicit recognition precedes explicit teaching\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Body learns before mind explains\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Points stated post-exercise (when nervous system regulated)\
- 
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Reinforced through story and application\
\
### Success Criteria\
\

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Chapter points appear in three forms (seed/experience/name) not one  \

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Seed appears before tension peak (implicit recognition)  \

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Name appears post-exercise (explicit integration)  \

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Punctuation creates emphasis (no SSML pauses needed)  \

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  Chapter points reinforced through story/carry sentence  \

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  System generates content automatically (not manual editing)  \
